Element	Function
Calcium (Ca²⁺)	Crucial for neurotransmitter release, synaptic plasticity
Sodium (Na⁺)	Generates action potentials in neurons
Potassium (K⁺)	Resets electrical state of neurons, essential for neural firing
Magnesium (Mg²⁺)	NMDA receptor regulation, brain protection
Chloride (Cl⁻)	Maintains membrane potential; GABA receptor function
Nitrogen (N)	Part of all amino acids and neurotransmitters (e.g., dopamine, serotonin)
Oxygen (O₂)	Vital for ATP (energy) production in brain mitochondria
Phosphorus (P)	Makes up DNA, ATP, and cell membranes (phospholipids)
